The Airship, Section B (KG) / lounge
Sonic49 | ??? 19-May-21 04:02 PM
A rather cozy place. In here is more or less a normal hotel lounge but with a slight color shift. A light gray, almost white wooden floor covers the whole room with no carpet in sight. The chairs and couches here are a bit darker (and so a bit more gray), but they fit the theme pretty well, and so do muted brown tables. There's even a TV here in one corner of the room, which actually has a remote that can be used to control it. The TV is functional and seems to be running a program that allows you to view a selection of movies and TV shows - in short, they're all PG-13 or under, and nothing about a Killing Game or Danganronpa is here. Don't try to get around this, it won't work. Well, everything seems normal... except for the windows. Looking out, you can clearly see the sky (or whatever's around you at the current moment) all around you - a sky that you can further explore in the #viewing-area, to which the entrance of that area is here. That's definitely unique. There's also stairs here. One section leads down to the #dorm-hallway, and one leads up to the Section A hallway, which only has one visible door: #goros-room. But why is all of this on an airship out of all places? (edited)

The smell of smoke is one he's been toughing through, but a moment's respite is something he's more than glad to take. "...?" He frowns. Isn't that rude to Jack, though? Doesn't that imply that David thinks he smells bad? David shakes his head and sits up straight, eye wiped clean, and continues taking deep breaths to make the last one less suspicious. He shifts uncomfortably, because it feels like he's inhaling smoke, even thought he isn't.
